  • Classes in org.neo4j.internal.schema used by org.neo4j.internal.schema 
    Class Description
    ConstraintDescriptor  
    ConstraintType
    The enum of all the types of constraints that we support.
    FulltextSchemaDescriptor
    Schema descriptors of this sub-type are guaranteed to be of IndexType.FULLTEXT, and capture index updates with PropertySchemaType.PARTIAL_ANY_TOKEN.
    IndexBehaviour  
    IndexCapability
    Capabilities of an index.
    IndexConfig
    The index configuration is an immutable map from Strings to Values.
    IndexDescriptor  
    IndexOrder
    Used to specify ordering of index query results, if index is capable of providing that order.
    IndexOrderCapability
    Describe the capability of an index to return the property values for a given query in order.
    IndexPrototype
    The prototype of an index that may or may not exist.
    IndexProviderDescriptor  
    IndexRef  
    IndexType
    This is the internal equivalent of IndexType.
    IndexValueCapability
    Describe the capability of an index to also return the exact property value for a given query.
    LabelSchemaDescriptor
    Schema descriptors of this sub-type are guaranteed to have exactly one label, and match index updates with PropertySchemaType.COMPLETE_ALL_TOKENS.
    PropertySchemaType
    This enum signifies how this schema should behave in regards to updates.
    RelationTypeSchemaDescriptor
    Schema descriptors of this sub-type are guaranteed to have exactly one relationship type, and match index updates with PropertySchemaType.COMPLETE_ALL_TOKENS.
    ReservedSchemaRuleNames
    This enum contains names that SchemaRule.getName() could perhaps return, but which are reserved for current or future internal use.
    SchemaDescriptor
    Internal representation of one schema unit, for example a label-property pair.
    SchemaDescriptorLookupSet.PropertyMultiSet
    A starting point for traversal of property key tokens.
    SchemaDescriptorLookupSet.PropertySet
    A single item in a property key chain.
    SchemaDescriptorSupplier  
    SchemaProcessor
    A SchemaProcessor performs from side-effect processing on a SchemaDescriptor.
    SchemaRule
    Represents a stored schema rule.
